==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*standan''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[standa]], Old High German [[stantan]], Old Saxon [[standan]], Old Norse [[standa]], Gothic [[𐍃𐍄𐌰𐌽𐌳𐌰𐌽]].  The Germanic source is cognate with Greek [[ἵστάναι]], Latin [[stare]], Old Irish [[tairissiur]], Old Slavic ''stojati'' (Russian [[стоять]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'standan/

===Verb===
'''standan''' (class VI strong: '''standeþ'''/'''stent''' ‘he stands’; '''stōd''' ‘he stood’; '''stōdon''' ‘they stood’; '''ġestanden''' past participle)
# to [[stand]]

